$interpreted: Dan Shan: Phew~ Finally shook 'em off... Let's stop here and get ourselves ready.
Nolva: Is this Mount Wark? Separating the East from the Kingdom of the Sun? I've never seen it before. It's so tall...
Dan Shan: Bwahaha, that's nothing. You're about to conquer this mountain!
Nolva: Conquer it? What do you mean?
Dan Shan: Why, we're gonna push right through it, of course! Once we've crossed the peak, you'll be able to head north from one of the Alliance ports.
Nolva: But I thought it was impossible to cross... Isn't that why the two kingdoms always needed to pass through the Desert Port?
Dan Shan: Heh, impossible for your average Joe, perhaps. But in our line of work there's always a few special tricks of the trade!
Dan Shan: Before we go, though, we have to make a few tweaks to the carriage. Once we've got everything in order, we'll ferry you over in a jiffy!
Nolva: ...Is your work always this dangerous?
Dan Shan: Yup, it's all in the job description~ Besides, it'd be bad karma if we could get away with this stuff too easily.
Excited Employee: Boss's right! We'll go anywhere the wind carries us~
Dan Shan: I've got work to do. I'll be back when I'm done.
Nolva: I knew Mr. Dan Shan and his team were good people.
Nolva: Ah, I forgot. You don't like such talk, do you, Hugo...
Hugo: I...
Nolva: Uh oh, there's monsters! We can't let them disturb Mr. Dan Shan!
Dan Shan: Bwahaha, I told you. With that fierce dude around, it's the monsters who should be afraid, not us.
Hugo: You're wrong. Monsters don't feel fear.
Dan Shan: All right, all right, fuhgeddaboudit. Everything's in order, let's get the cargo onboard!
Dan Shan: Hold tight, it's about to get bumpy.
Dan Shan: Ha—Flying nun mode, engage!
Dan Shan: Three!
Dan Shan: Two!
Dan Shan: One! Shoot!
Nolva: Amazing! We're really crossing Mount Wark!
Dan Shan: Feels good to have someone who appreciates my work!
Dan Shan: The Hunky King's a pro. There's no mountain I can't cross!
Nolva: Wh-what was that?!
Dan Shan: Insects? What are they doing here?!
Ambushing Insect Soldier: —Kill them! Crush the Eastern Alliance!
Dan Shan: Cut 'em off with the smoke, boys! Don't let the little lady come to any harm!
Dan Shan: Maniacs!
Hugo: A senseless massacre—Evil must be punished.
Hugo: So, why were they lying in wait for us?
Dan Shan: I was about to ask you. You're pretty unbothered by it all...
Baa Baa: Waaah! My hero~
Baa Baa: You're a real fierce one, eh? No need for us to help out, looks like.
Dan Shan: ...Is that Baa Baa? I was wondering who else would be so brave as to hide away and watch from the sidelines.
Baa Baa: Ehh? I didn't want to get lost in the fray. Just imagine if hadn't recognized me and taken me for an enemy, then I'd be toast~
Nolva: Do you know this lady, Mr. Dan Shan?
Dan Shan: Well, you could say we've done business together.
Dan Shan: It's been a minute. Have you gotten bigger?
Baa Baa: I've made myself some dosh, with a little help from my friends~
Dan Shan: Don't be so modest, I'm sure the Alliance pays real well. If I'd known about it earlier I'd have asked you to pull a few strings for me, too.
Baa Baa: You must be pulling my leg, mate~ I'd never dare refuse a request from the Alliance~
Baa Baa: And this time's no different. The Arbiter asked me to come help ya out.
Nolva: Huh? You mean the East Alliance knows we're coming?
Baa Baa: Course they do, the Arbiter's no drongo!
Hugo: (Could this be the First... no, the True Sun's doing...?)
Dan Shan: Enough of a drongo not to send more forces to meet us... But that said, the Alliance must be in real trouble if they're sending you out to be a soldier now.
Baa Baa: (Guh~ I only made it out alive thanks to that beast of a commander, but...)
Baa Baa: Maybe I just had a stroke of good fortune, ya know? Look~
Baa Baa: It was the Alliance forces' orders to wipe out these Insect soldiers, but this champ took 'em all out without breaking a sweat, ka-pow, and without a single casualty, too!
Nolva: So the Insects were planning to lie in wait and ambush you here?
Baa Baa: Sure looks like it~ But I've got no clue how they knew we were coming...
Dan Shan: Whatever, our work is done here either way.
Dan Shan: It was a pleasure doing business with you both... Miss Nolva, Mister Fierceface. I have other commissions to be getting on with, money to be made~ Take care!
Nolva: Thank you, Mister Dan Shan... It was quite a journey. You take care, too.
Dan Shan: Oh, you bet I will.
Dan Shan: What? Wasn't that a cool enough send-off?
Grumbling Employee: Oh yeah, very cool. But that girl didn't even give you a second look...
Dan Shan: —What do you know?! True heroes don't do it for the applause, you know! Get out of here, go check on the carriage! Scram! The sooner we're out of here, the sooner we can celebrate!
Agitated Employee: All right~ I'm dying for a stiff drink! Let's go!
Dan Shan: —This was a hard journey for our dependable little vehicle, too. Let's see if our baby's caught any scratches...
Dan Shan: Hey... Hey now... Don't do anything rash. Talk to me.
???: Silence.
???: I'll only ask once—What are you to the Dracontines?
